originalText.text: They refused to honor my Park Whiz booking  for Queen on 10/12.  An attendant claimed the location was completely full &, instead, banged on my car — scaring me & my daughter— while telling me to back up. I told him that I had a prepaid reservation & he, very loudly, told me that he didn’t care & to leave. Well, I care. It’s my money, which you are keeping, it’s breach of contract & when someone makes a reservation & pays for it, the place is supposed to honor it. These people are thieves. Stay away.  They deserve negative stars, one for each dollar of mine they want to keep.

originalText.text: They have cars going in and out one way and make people reverse down the one way street on 32nd which is extremely dangerous. When I pulled my car into the overpacked garage, they then started to yell at me to move my car into a spot I couldn’t fit into and ended up scratching my car. Employee continue to scream at me in front of my 5 year old child. I park in garages in the city all the time and I’ve never experienced this level of disorganization and rudeness. Photo of rude employee verbally harassing me included. It was insane!

originalText.text: Another excellent facility from City Park. I pre-paid and had absolutely no problems or extra fees. Very nice people working and clean facility. Great location! Right across the street from MSG.  5 Minutes to drop off car, 15 minutes to pick it up.

originalText.text:
DO NOT PARK HERE!!! I used an Icon parking coupon for a discounted price, during its valid time period. Attendant indicated he would accept the pass prior to parking. When I returned to the garage, he denies this confirmation and charged me a full days price for a two hour stay. Very rude and very dishonest.

UPDATE:  I contacted the main office to dispute the charge. The garage does not honor coupons if you are attending an MSG event. Fair enough, but I did not go to an MSG event on this day and I provided evidence of the school event I attended for 2 hours. The resolution was a $15 refund, charging me for an allotment of up to a 6 hour stay. Its complete BS, but it was the only compromise they were willing to make with me.

Bottom line: Save your money and find another parking garage in the area. There are NO guarantees with the policy here!
